body: Hey @BenMorel, can you reproduce the issue on https://psalm.dev ?

Wow, thank you so much @muglug, I couldn't expect any better or faster ;-)

Looking forward to using it! :tada:

Looks like this doesn't work yet: https://psalm.dev/r/4e7c6e421d

Even though the related commit has been released now. Any reason why?

@BenMorel it works, as soon as Psalm can see at least one usage of the class and with the right config enabled: https://psalm.dev/r/680a180631

EDIT: and because it's private, I think it was working even before this change. It seems that this change was focused on public properties

@orklah What's the right config? We use Psalm level 1, and Psalm never detects an unused private property, even when the class is in use.

Is it because these classes are injected via DI, so never instantiated via their constructor explicitly?

@BenMorel do you have findUnusedCode="true" in your config?

I don't think the DI is an issue, Psalm doesn't look for explicit instantiation, it looks for any method call, so as long as Psalm doesn't tell you to get rid of the class completely, it should also detect unused properties

@orklah Sorry, I didn't know that some inspections had to be enabled explicitly. I thought that level 1 had all of them enabled.

It works fine now, thank you!
